   <descr>
      <p>"You're in Love" was a single released by Wilson Phillips,
    their fourth single from their debut album 
    <i>Wilson Phillips</i>.</p>
      <p>"You're in Love" was number one on the Billboard Hot 100 for
    one week, ending April 20, 1991. It was the their third number
    one hit and fourth top 5 single. It also spent four weeks atop
    the adult contemporary chart in 1991, the group's longest stay
    at #1 on this chart (both "Hold On" and "Release Me" reached #1
    on the AC chart for one week each).</p>
      <p>With this single, the group received a nomination on the
    Grammy Awards of 1992 in the Best Pop Vocal Performance by a
    Duo or Group category, losing to R.E.M.'s "Losing My Religion"
    .</p>
